{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5384", "repo": "rails", "body": "@josevalim I've added back the initialize method as ActiveModel::MassAssignment. It's anemic for now but will grow as people find need for mass assignment security and the other ActiveRecord like methods (`attributes=`, `assign_attributes`). This is such a common piece of code that there's no reason to believe that people needing mass assignment functionality also need to support the ActiveModel API, provided by BasicModel. For example, [this presentation](http://decoupling-wrocloverb-2012.heroku.com/) repeats the code twice in classes that never interface with ActionPack.", "_id": {"$oid": "52381901bd3543c15100e101"}, "issue_id": 5384, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4500142", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5384#issuecomment-4500142", "updated_at": "2012-03-14T15:18:42Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cgriego/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cgriego/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cgriego/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cgriego/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/cgriego", "login": "cgriego", "gravatar_id": "2d643c10e432e230c9d4bf97d15d6a46", "html_url": "https://github.com/cgriego", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cgriego/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cgriego/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cgriego/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/2d643c10e432e230c9d4bf97d15d6a46?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fa821a161aa4214f5ff5b8ca372960ebb.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cgriego/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 4805, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cgriego/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-03-14T15:18:42Z", "id": 4500142, "owner": "rails"}
